House Resolution 135
By: Representative Hong of the 103rd
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing February 3, 2025, as Topical Steroid Withdrawal Syndrome Awareness Day at
2 the state capitol; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Topical Steroid Withdrawal Syndrome (TSWS), also known as Topical Steroid
4 Addiction or Red Skin Syndrome, is a severe and debilitating condition that can arise from
5 intentional or unintentional exposure to topical steroids; and
6 WHEREAS, topical steroids are widely prescribed and available over the counter to treat
7 both acute and chronic skin conditions, including eczema, psoriasis, vitiligo, and alopecia
8 areata; and
9 WHEREAS, TSWS is characterized by severe symptoms such as skin flushing,
10 inflammation, diffuse spreading rashes, profuse skin flaking, and intense burning and itching
11 that often surpass the severity of the original condition, typically manifesting after the use
12 of topical steroids, between treatments, or upon discontinuation; and
13 WHEREAS, recovery from TSWS can take several months to several years, leaving many
14 sufferers bedridden or housebound and unable to work, care for children, or attend school;
15 and
